---
import DocLayout from '@layouts/DocLayout.astro';
import { withBase } from '@/data/navigation';

const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
---
<DocLayout
  title="Referências"
  description="Bibliografia consolidada do site evidências clínicas. Livros, artigos, recursos online e diretrizes citados ao longo do conteúdo."
>
  <h1>Referências</h1>

  <p>
    Bibliografia consolidada do site, organizada por tipo. Cada página individual mantém suas próprias
    referências numeradas; esta lista reúne as fontes recorrentes e mais importantes.
  </p>

  <h2 id="livros-texto-fundamentais-de-mbe">Livros-texto fundamentais de MBE</h2>

  <p>
    Straus SE, Glasziou P, Richardson WS, Haynes RB. <em>Evidence-Based Medicine: How to Practice and
    Teach EBM</em>. 5ª ed. Edinburgh: Elsevier; 2018.
  </p>

  <p>
    Heneghan C, Badenoch D. <em>Evidence-Based Medicine Toolkit</em>. 2ª ed. Oxford: BMJ Books /
    Blackwell; 2006.
  </p>

  <p>
    Greenhalgh T. <em>How to Read a Paper: The Basics of Evidence-Based Medicine and Healthcare</em>.
    6ª ed. Hoboken: Wiley-Blackwell; 2019.
  </p>

  <p>
    Guyatt G, Rennie D, Meade MO, Cook DJ. <em>Users' Guides to the Medical Literature: A Manual for
    Evidence-Based Clinical Practice</em>. 3ª ed. New York: McGraw-Hill; 2014.
  </p>

  <p>
    Sackett DL, Haynes RB, Guyatt GH, Tugwell P. <em>Clinical Epidemiology: A Basic Science for
    Clinical Medicine</em>. 2ª ed. Boston: Little, Brown; 1991.
  </p>

  <h2 id="epidemiologia-e-metodos-de-pesquisa">Epidemiologia e métodos de pesquisa</h2>

  <p>
    Rothman KJ, Greenland S, Lash TL. <em>Modern Epidemiology</em>. 4ª ed. Philadelphia: Lippincott
    Williams & Wilkins; 2021.
  </p>

  <p>Porta M, ed. <em>A Dictionary of Epidemiology</em>. 6ª ed. Oxford: Oxford University Press; 2014.</p>

  <p>
    Higgins JPT, Thomas J, Chandler J, et al, eds. <em>Cochrane Handbook for Systematic Reviews of
    Interventions</em> version 6.4. Cochrane; 2023. Disponível em:
    <a href="https://training.cochrane.org/handbook" rel="noopener" target="_blank">training.cochrane.org/handbook</a>
  </p>

  <h2 id="cognicao-clinica-e-comunicacao">Cognição clínica e comunicação</h2>

  <p>
    Kahneman D. <em>Rápido e Devagar: Duas Formas de Pensar</em>. Rio de Janeiro: Objetiva; 2012.
    (<em>Thinking, Fast and Slow</em>. New York: Farrar, Straus and Giroux; 2011)
  </p>

  <p>
    Schön DA. <em>The Reflective Practitioner: How Professionals Think in Action</em>. New York:
    Basic Books; 1983.
  </p>

  <p>
    Eve R. <em>PUNs and DENs: Discovering Learning Needs in General Practice</em>. Oxford: Radcliffe
    Publishing; 2003.
  </p>

  <h2 id="rastreamento-e-prevencao">Rastreamento e prevenção</h2>

  <p>
    Wilson JMG, Jungner G. <em>Principles and Practice of Screening for Disease</em>. Geneva: World
    Health Organization; 1968.
    <a href="https://iris.who.int/handle/10665/37650" rel="noopener" target="_blank">iris.who.int/handle/10665/37650</a>
  </p>

  <p>
    Raffle AE, Mackie A, Gray JAM. <em>Screening: Evidence and Practice</em>. 2ª ed. Oxford: Oxford
    University Press; 2019.
  </p>

  <p>
    UK National Screening Committee. <em>Criteria for a population screening programme</em>. 2022.
    <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/evidence-review-criteria-national-screening-programmes" rel="noopener" target="_blank">gov.uk</a>
  </p>

  <p>
    World Health Organization. <em>Screening programmes: a short guide</em>. WHO Regional Office for
    Europe; 2020.
    <a href="https://iris.who.int/handle/10665/330829" rel="noopener" target="_blank">iris.who.int/handle/10665/330829</a>
  </p>

  <h2 id="forcas-tarefa-e-diretrizes">Forças-tarefa e diretrizes</h2>

  <p>
    U.S. Preventive Services Task Force. <em>Procedure Manual</em>.
    <a href="https://www.uspreventiveservicestaskforce.org/uspstf/about-uspstf/methods-and-processes/procedure-manual" rel="noopener" target="_blank">uspreventiveservicestaskforce.org</a>
  </p>

  <p>
    Canadian Task Force on Preventive Health Care. <em>Methods</em>.
    <a href="https://canadiantaskforce.ca/methods/" rel="noopener" target="_blank">canadiantaskforce.ca/methods</a>
  </p>

  <p>
    National Institute for Health and Care Excellence. <em>Developing NICE guidelines: the manual</em>.
